<div id="review_1897182531" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1897182531" />
    <a title="Kaitlin" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/51394271-kaitlin"><img alt="Kaitlin" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1571455622p2/51394271.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1897182531?book_show_action=true">Mar 18, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Kaitlin" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Kaitlin" href="/user/show/51394271-kaitlin">Kaitlin</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Hardcover 9780060088941" href="/book/show/2919218-the-dark-bride">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1897182531" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer18029609432370302693">I have heard great things about Laura Restrepo, so going into this book I admit that I had high hopes. I wish that i would have read this in Spanish because I feel that is the best way to soak in her realism. <br/><br/>Restrepo told an intriguing love story between a &quot;puta&quot; (prostitute) and a &quot;petrolero&quot; (oil worker) while exposing the struggles of the people and the way Americans exploited Colombia at the time. You learn how being a prostitute was really the only choice for a poor Colombian girl and how </span>
  <span id="freeText18029609432370302693" style="display:none">I have heard great things about Laura Restrepo, so going into this book I admit that I had high hopes. I wish that i would have read this in Spanish because I feel that is the best way to soak in her realism. <br /><br />Restrepo told an intriguing love story between a "puta" (prostitute) and a "petrolero" (oil worker) while exposing the struggles of the people and the way Americans exploited Colombia at the time. You learn how being a prostitute was really the only choice for a poor Colombian girl and how they dealt with having to sleep with strangers in order to have the bare necessities. Restrepo also does a great job in depicting the strikes that many oil workers participated in to change working conditions, even if it meant losing their jobs or in more extreme situations .. their lives. <br /><br /><br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="18029609432370302693" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


